item.title: Ela Minus, Franz Ferdinand and Damon Locks
item.description:
KEXP DJ Abbie joins host Evie Stokes to talk about Ela Minus getting her through the pandemic, and Minus' new album. Plus, you'll hear all about Abbie's Franz Ferdinand fan card! KEXP music director Chris Sanley shares a new song from Chicago multidisciplinary artist Damon Locks.

Songs featured:

  1. Ela Minus – “Upwards”
  2. Franz Ferdinand – “The Doctor”
  3. Damon Locks - “Click”

item.title: Smokey Robinson
item.description: In this special episode of the R&B Money Podcast, Tank and J. Valentine are joined by the legendary Smokey Robinson. Celebrating 50 years of his classic album "Quiet Storm," Smokey opens up about his journey in the music industry, the stories behind his most beloved songs, and his thoughts on the evolution of R&B music. Watch as Smokey discusses his profound impact on the genre and shares personal anecdotes from his time at Motown. Subscribe and tune in to witness a master at work...
